# Check the updates on
# http://github.com/chexov/unixscripts/tree/master/aws-cli/

Description
===========
This scripts may help you to install all the AWS tools in one shot
in your home dir.
And will run them from that place and not from /usr/local.



Installation
============
mkdir ~/amazon
cp profile ~/amazon/
cp update-tools.sh ~/amazon/
~/amazon/update-tools.sh

To apply the environment:
. ~/amazon/profile

You may want add this line to your ~/.profile, I guess..

Have a happy day.

